This paper discusses a framework for log anonymization and information management, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the modularity and flexibility of the framework, which suggests that it may involve database systems (cs.DB) and machine learning techniques (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the trade-offs between information loss and privacy/security concerns, which suggests that it may involve software engineering (cs.SE) and cyber security (cs.CY).
